,\"text\":\"**Thinking about file paths and package names**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the test file path should be one-to-one. Maybe I need to change the package name since `com.esotericsoftware_kryo_shaded` isn't the same as `com.esotericsoftware.kryo`. I'm thinking about how the filter with `includeClasses \\\"com.esotericsoftware.**\\\"` might not include the underscore segment, but it seems like that's not the right assumption. Hm, it might require a different approach. Let’s figure out how to navigate this issue!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test coverage**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the metadata being untracked, but the user specifically asked about tests. So maybe I should focus on improving test coverage? Wait, I need to clarify whether the user truly wants that. I also suspect that the coverage report likely comes from JaCoCo for JVM rather than something native. I’ll need to double-check that to ensure I’m on the right track. I want to be sure I understand everything before proceeding!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating constructor behavior**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the instance's value asserts correctly. If the native `getDeclared` succeeds and `constructor.newInstance()` works, it should pass too. I think it might be best to keep the `PrivateNoArgType` constructor private and ensure the field is final. Oh, and will Jacoco cover line 1253 from the JVM? It seems like it will. I’m also thinking about whether to remove the ineffective KryoSerializable fallback, which might simplify things.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Nec58o4QCGmYk5A5qjqxfjaS|fc_06b8248c32871bc70169f291bca01081968ee0df9f8ce1bc9a", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.esotericsoftware/kryo-shaded/3.0.3/src/test/java/com_esotericsoftware/kryo_shaded/KryoInnerDefaultInstantiatorStrategyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void delegatesToFallbackAfterReflectionFindsNoNoArgConstructor() {\n        boolean previousAndroidFlag = Util.isAndroid;\n        Util.isAndroid = true;\n        try {\n            Kryo.DefaultInstantiatorStrategy strategy = new Kryo.DefaultInstantiatorStrategy(new NullFallbackStrategy());\n\n            ObjectInstantiator<?> instantiator = strategy.newInstantiatorOf(KryoSerializable.class);\n\n            assertThat(instantiator.newInstance()).isNull();\n        } finally {\n            Util.isAndroid = previousAndroidFlag;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class NullFallbackStrategy implements InstantiatorStrategy {\n        @Override\n        public <T> ObjectInstantiator<T> newInstantiatorOf(Class<T> type) {\n            return new ObjectInstantiator<T>() {\n                @Override\n                public T newInstance() {\n                    return null;\n                }\n            };\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void createsPrivateNoArgTypeUsingDeclaredConstructorWhenReflectAsmIsBypassed() {\n        boolean previousAndroidFlag = Util.isAndroid;\n        Util.isAndroid = true;\n        try {\n            Kryo.DefaultInstantiatorStrategy strategy = new Kryo.DefaultInstantiatorStrategy(new DirectFallbackStrategy());\n\n            @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n            ObjectInstantiator<PrivateNoArgType> instantiator = strategy.newInstantiatorOf(PrivateNoArgType.class);\n            PrivateNoArgType instance = instantiator.newInstance();\n\n            assertThat(instance.value).isEqualTo(\"created\");\n        } finally {\n            Util.isAndroid = previousAndroidFlag;\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void delegatesToFallbackAfterReflectionFindsNoNoArgConstructor() {\n        boolean previousAndroidFlag = Util.isAndroid;\n        Util.isAndroid = true;\n        try {\n            Kryo.DefaultInstantiatorStrategy strategy = new Kryo.DefaultInstantiatorStrategy(new NullFallbackStrategy());\n\n            ObjectInstantiator<?> instantiator = strategy.newInstantiatorOf(KryoSerializable.class);\